ondering what classes are most needed.  He likes to log on and find a group right away, so he likes to play whatever class is most in demand.<br><br>I myself will probably play a magician--unless 3/4 of the server is already playing mages, lol, how's the magician population?<br><br>Are there channels that people use to form groups?  I was hoping somebody could tell me the more popular channels.<br><br>About the trivial loot code--as I understand this (a kind person tried to explain this to me last night), anything that is magic or lore will not drop if you are not the right level to get experience from the mob.  However, there are not any nodrop items, except epics and the like.  Is that about right?<br><br>Sorry for all the questions but I'm just anxious to get it right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And thanks to all the people I met last night, especially Biena.  <br><br>Gemm/Gemmima <br>Lost Legacy<br>test server<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 489<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 6:02:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silly new player questions</span><hr size=1> When the Firiona Vie server first started, everyone automatically had /roleplay on (you couldn't turn it off).  They later changed it so you can toggle it, but most people still leave it on.<br><br>If someone's level/class is hidden, and their name is blue (or red), they're /anon.<br><br>If someone's level/class is hidden, and their name is purple (or orange), they're /roleplay.<br><br>(People who are PvP+ have red/orange names, but that's all of maybe 1 or 2 people on the server, and probably by accident).<br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=grumgor>Grumgor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 6:10:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silly new player questions</span><hr size=1> The only server wide channel that I'm aware of is &quot;market&quot;, which is basically the server-wide out of character-auction channel. (I don't mean ooc, but an auction channel that is not in-character... the primary role of the channel is still auction)<br><br>Mages are not common, so by all means play a mage. A word of advice: get into Najena and whereever else you need to go for focus items soon, because the TLC code makes it impossible to get after you are higher in level. Lots of the mages that do exist are stuck by this.<br><br>Enjoy FV <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uavuna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avuna</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 6:44:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~kingdomslost/unda2L.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silly new player questions</span><hr size=1> Figured I'd put my 2 cp worth in here.<br><br> I had heard that Firiona Vie is set up by alignment, meaning if I take my evil little inkie shadowknight out to the commons and try to group with some lovey dovey Marr cleric, it won't be allowed.  <br><br> Is this true?   <p><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~kingdomslost/avunasig.jpg"><BR><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=245155">Avuna</A>  <BR><i>For thou too heinous a respect didst hold of man, too little heed of powers divine!  And us the Fates, the ancients of the earth, didst deem as nothing worth.  Scornful to me thou art, yet shalt not fend my wrath from him; though unto hell he flee, there too are we! </i> ~Aeschlus, The Furies~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 492<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 6:48:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silly new player questions</span><hr size=1>    <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Used</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to be true.  The alignment restriction rules were removed a few weeks back (for no good reason, many would argue).  You can group w/ anyone you want now.  Expect mocking for wierd combinations though (I teased a troll in Highpass who was grouped w/ some gnomes for playing with his food).<br><br>- Syll / Kat <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usimanmistrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SimanMistrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 120<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/02 6:49:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silly new player questions</span><hr size=1> They removed the alignment restrictions--shadowknights are able to group with paladins to their heart's content if they choose.<br><br>Sadistik<br>Level 14 Rogue<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=278078">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=278078</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Siman<br>Level 55 Druid (Retired) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uteapray.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teapray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 2:20:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silly new player questions</span><hr size=1> And High Elf clerics can finally be with their Beloved Ogre warriors!  I am glad that the Gods let me walk my own path, despite the disapproval of those whom I would hold dear.<br><br>Teapray <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uteiraa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>teiraa</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Innoruuk also needs love</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 2:57:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/38/38498/pages/89050/teiraa3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silly new player questions</span><hr size=1> A shadowknight could group with a good paladin even before the patch. But it was necessary to have a neutral person in the group as well.<br>Many of you know that I'm playing a (rather) good necromancer, and yes, I am grouping with paladins sometimes. But still I prefer to have a neutral person in the group to moderate, if any issues come up (which happens quite often).<br>So personally I still think the old rules were better, actually. But of course, I respect that High Elven clerics want to group with ogre warriors. Nevertheless, even before the patch paladins and high elven clerics were able to chose neutral-good alignment and thus group with evil-aligned characters. Or am I wrong? Never tried it at that time.... <p><i><b>Teiraa Shadowflower</b> <br>The Friendly(TM) Dark Elf Necromancer <br>The Twilight Bastion<br>@Firiona Vie <br></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukistanilay.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kistanilay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/2/02 8:03:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2223.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Silly new player questions</span><hr size=1> ROFL Syllestrae, playing with his food!  LOL TY for the good laugh.  Good comedy.<br><br>Kist <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion